TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents the N-terminal hydrophobic region
CC   (approximately 26-29 residues, positions 1-29) of RnfB, the subunit
CC   B of the ion-translocating oxidoreductase complex (Rnf/Rsx complex).
CC   This region likely anchors the RnfB protein to the membrane and
CC   precedes the FeS domain (Pfam:PF04060) and ferredoxin domains
CC   (Pfam:PF14697). The Rnf complex couples electron transfer with ion
CC   translocation across membranes. The family is found predominantly in
CC   Bacillota (Clostridia, Clostridiaceae, Peptostreptococcaceae) and
CC   Pseudomonadota (Gammaproteobacteria).
RN   [1]
RM   36274063
RT   Purification and structural characterization of the
RT   Na(+)-translocating ferredoxin: NAD(+) reductase (Rnf) complex of
RT   Clostridium tetanomorphum.
RA   Vitt S, Prinz S, Eisinger M, Ermler U, Buckel W;
RL   Nat Commun 2022;13:6315.
